==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parry
<hw>Par"ry</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧r"r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Parried</conjf>
<pr>(p⟦acr⟧r"r⟦ecr⟧d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Parrying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>par⟦eacute⟧</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>parer</ets>. See <er>Pare</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To ward off; to stop, or to turn aside; <as>as, to
<ex>parry</ex> a thrust, a blow, or anything that means or threatens
harm</as>.</def> <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Vice <qex>parries</qex> wide⟦br⟧
The undreaded volley with a sword of straw.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To avoid; to shift or put off; to evade.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The French government has <qex>parried</qex> the payment of our
claims.</q> <rj><qau>E. Everett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>parry</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: parry
<hw>par"ry</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To ward off, evade, or turn aside
something, as a blow, argument, etc.</def> <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>parry</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: parry
<hw>par"ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Parries</plw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>A warding off of a thrust or blow, as in
sword and bayonet exercises or in boxing; hence, figuratively, a
defensive movement in debate or other intellectual encounter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

